# get_account_history_by_operations

##### Explanation：Query the recent transaction records of the account based on oeration_type, support visiting next page and returning the txID corresponding to the operataion

##### usage: get_account_history_by_operations \[\] start limit_num

##### Parameter：account_name_or_id, \[\], start, limit_num

| Parameter | Explanation |
| :--- | :--- |
| account_name_or_id | Account name or id |
| \[\] | operation_type，for example if the transfer is 0, you can enter \[0\]. If the argument is "", it means to query all the operation_type |
| start | Staring serial number, similar to get_relative_account_history |
| limit_num | Display recent "limit" transaction records |
